column5: Had to head up to Innisfil today so I stopped at a few Cook's Bay access points and it doesn't look good! The east wind was blowing pretty good and oddly the further north I went the less ice there was! And with the forecasted weather for the next couple of days is not going to help! We're going to have to wait a little longer Misfish! I guess if we're going anywhere this weekend we better go further north! LOL Stay safe out there!
Theres no white fish there anyways David. Im not concerned. LOL + 7 today,then -8 Saturday. WTH
Our weather just gets crazier & crazier but it's the winds that need to die down along with the colder temps! Hope that you & your family had a Great Holiday Season!

If we get a a few days of no wind and -10 or more, the whole lake would set up. I have not seen any mist/steam ,coming off the water for a long time. It,s ready to harden up.  I know my feet would like a break from the waders and the cold river waters.
Come on you guys. Suck it up, get your spud bars out and give us an ice fishing report?
Well tell you what, you stick out your feet and we'll get out our spud bars and give them a poke and watch you dance like a cod jigging ______. ?
I saw a bunch of Simcoe Whities at  the candlelight Christmas Eve service praying for warm weather. See, there is a God.
